				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\Delta \eta \times \Delta \phi = 0.1 \times 0.1$$\end{document} in the first two radial layers, called layers A and BC (just layer B in the EB), and Δη×Δϕ=0.2×0.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
