				\begin{document}$$\Delta \eta \times \Delta \phi = 0.2 \times 0.1$$\end{document} in the third layer, referred to as layer D. The projective layout of cells and naming convention are shown in Fig. 1. The so-called ITC cells (D4, C10 and E-cells) are located between the LB and EB, and provide coverage in the range 0.8<|η|<1.6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
